title: Grateful Dead Live at McNichols Sports Arena on 1994-11-30
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray;, Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, Queen Jane Approximately, Lazy River Road, Me & My Uncle*-> Big River*, Loose Lucy, Cassidy

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime, Samba In The Rain, Crazy Fingers, Estimated Prophet-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Space-> I Need A Miracle-> Standing On the Moon-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Liberty

* Weir on acoustic guitar

reviews.review_text:
27 years done come and gone my oh my! I was at this show 27 years ago tonight. While I had fun and it wasnt immediately apparent at the time, this is probably the worst GD show I saw out of 30+.
I'll give you two facts that support my conclusion, although a single listen will suffice...
The Cassidy, Crazy Fingers, Estimated,, Loose Lucy, Miracle, Queen Jane, Samba, SOTM, Terrapin, Touch, and West L.A. are ALL the shortest or next to shortest versions of the year. The band is clearly not engaged and just punching the clock on this night.
Jerry completely misses the 'Inspiration' line in Terrapin. That about sums up this night in Denver...missing inspiration.
McNichols didn't have the best acoustics, but this is a respectable AUD.
